# Environment Configuration

## Development Environment Variables

### Frontend Configuration

**File**: `.env.local` (create in `frontend/` directory)

```env
# Backend API Base URL
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Use mock data for development (true/false)
VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=true
```

### Available Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `VITE_API_URL` | `http://localhost:3000` | Backend API endpoint |
| `VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA` | `true` | Enable mock data generation for development |

## Production Build Environment

For production deployment, set:

```env
VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-domain.com
VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=false
```

## Build Configuration

The Vite configuration automatically reads these variables and injects them at build time.

To use environment variables in code:

```typescript
const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || 'http://localhost:3000';
const useMockData = import.meta.env.VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA !== 'false';
```
